On Mon, 5 Aug 2002, Jim Hood wrote:

> I asked my local VW mechanic what he thought I should do.  He suggested that
> I stick a little bead of JB Stick Weld in each dowel hole, then place the
> dowel pins in.  This seemed to raise them up to what I think they should
> look like.  I guess I'll know in a few thousand miles if this works!!

I don't know if it would be a good idea to use JB weld for this purpose.
I'd rather have something more solid and exact.  You could make
metal shims to go in the bottom of the holes before the dowel pins go in,
filing the shims to get exactly the right projection of the pins.

George Lyle

